diaGrabber.source.libreOfficeCalc¶

class diaGrabber.source.libreOfficeCalc.libreOfficeCalc(ODS_file_name, sheet_name_or_number, data_type='unknown', print_error_when_cell_is_empty=False)[source]¶

allow to read values from a libre/open-office-calc document

Parameters:
  • ODS_file_name – “name of the file” e.g. “myfile.ods”
  • sheet_name_or_number – “name” OR number of the sheet e.g. “sheet1” OR 4
  • data_type – default “unknown”, all possible values are defined in diaGrabber.source._source.source._evalDataType()
  • print_error_when_cell_is_empty – default False, True Stopping readout and raise an error whenn one of all cells in the given cell_range is empty
basisDimension(name, resolution, cell_range, includeMethod='')¶

Add a new basis-dimension to the source. See diaGrabber.source._dimension.basisDimension for further explanation and options.

Parameters:
  • name (string) – [... of the dimension] e.g. “time”
  • resolution (int) – [number of tracked values of the dimension] e.g. 100
  • cell_range (string) – [“START:STOP”] range of the cells in the ods-file e.g. “C2:C1000” or “A1:E10”
  • includeMethod (string) – method to border the value-range, see diaGrabber.source._source.basisDimension.evalIncludeMethod() for all options
mergeDimension(name, cell_range, mergeMethod=None)¶

Add a new merge-dimension to the source. See diaGrabber.source._source.mergeDimension for further explanation and options.

Parameters:
  • name (string) – ... of the dimension e.g. “time”
  • resolution (int) – number of tracked values of the dimension e.g. 100
  • cell_range (string) – “START:STOP” range of the cells in the ods-file e.g. “C2:C1000” or “A1:E10”
  • mergeMethod (class from diaGrabber.methods.merge) – defines way of handle merge-values in the same place in the target are.
